ency%20and%20higher%20profit%20margins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20taking%20over%20in%202021%2C%20he's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-cuts-jobs-fashion-fitness-group-internal-messages-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslashed%3C%2Fa%3E%20jobs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-revamps-pay-structure-rewards-high-performing-employees-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevamped%3C%2Fa%3E%20pay%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-plan-cut-managers-aws-internal-guidelines-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrimmed%3C%2Fa%3E%20management%20layers%2C%20and%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-bend-curve-project-purges-billions-product-listings-everything-store-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereconsidered%3C%2Fa%3E%20Amazon's%20product%20listing%20approach%2C%20all%20in%20the%20name%20of%20saving%20money%20and%20driving%20efficiency.%20Amazon%20reported%20record%20profit%20of%20%2459%20billion%20in%202024%2C%20nearly%20double%20its%202023%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHolding%20the%20hiring%20budget%20steady%20could%20encourage%20Amazon%20retail%20managers%20to%20get%20smarter%20and%20more%20flexible%20with%20compensation%20expenses.%20HR%20professionals%20say%20budget-based%20planning%20offers%20tighter%20financial%20control%20than%20headcount%20targets.%20That%20can%20be%20useful%20in%20uncertain%20business%20environments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228637be6c-d662-4864-9c87-597ae29f0494%5C%22%3EStaying%20within%20limits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20email%20said%20Amazon%20retail%20CEO%20Doug%20Herrington%20inspected%20operating%20expenses%20%26quot%3Bvery%20closely%20throughout%20the%20last%20two%20years.%26quot%3B%20The%20retail%20organization%20also%20recently%20launched%20new%20financial%20reporting%20and%20analysis%20tools%20for%20tracking%20headcount%20and%20operating%20expenses.%20Some%20of%20the%20new%20features%20include%20the%20ability%20to%20plan%20headcount%20mix%20by%20job%20level%2C%20technical%20skills%2C%20and%20tenure%2C%20according%20to%20the%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20has%20been%20on%20a%20yearslong%20cost-cutting%20spree.%20After%20booming%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20online%20retail%20and%20cloud%20giant's%20growth%20slowed%2C%20triggering%20cutbacks%20in%20warehouse%20growth%20and%20the%20closure%20of%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-grand-challenge-moonshots-lab-shut-down-3-confidential-projects-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexperimental%20ventures%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeadcount%20has%20also%20leveled%20off.%20The%20company%20doubled%20its%20workforce%20to%201.6%20million%20from%202019%20to%202021%2C%20but%20that%20number%20dipped%20to%201.55%20million%20last%20year.%20Amazon%20has%20cut%20at%20least%2027%2C000%20employees%20since%20late%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManaging%20headcount%20instead%20of%20a%20hiring%20budget%20lets%20managers%20bring%20on%20high-cost%20talent%20without%20worrying%20much%20about%20salary%2C%20David%20Kryscynski%2C%20a%20human%20resources%20professor%20at%20Rutgers%2C%20told%20BI.%20But%20with%20a%20fixed%20labor%20budget%2C%20he%20said%2C%20managers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20stay%20within%20financial%20limits%2C%20either%20by%20hiring%20less%20or%20opting%20for%20lower-cost%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20model%20also%20gives%20managers%20more%20staffing%20flexibility%2C%20said%20Shaun%20Pichler%2C%20a%20management%20professor%20at%20California%20State%20University%2C%20Fullerton.%20Without%20headcount%20targets%2C%20they%20can%20bring%20on%20cheaper%20contractors%20or%20temporary%20workers.%20And%20they're%20not%20pressured%20to%20spend%20the%20full%20budget%2C%20often%20resulting%20in%20leaner%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTech%20firms%20have%20more%20widely%20adopted%20OpEx%20targets%20post-pandemic%20for%20largely%20the%20same%20reasons%20%E2%80%94%20high%20labor%20costs%2C%20reduced%20revenues%2C%20and%20to%20give%20managers%20more%20flexibility%2C%26quot%3B%20Pichler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon's%20retail%20arm%20remains%20laser-focused%20on%20cutting%20costs.%20At%20an%20internal%20all-hands%20meeting%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20retail%20chief%20Doug%20Herrington%20told%20employees%20that%20belt-tightening%20would%20likely%20extend%20into%202025%2C%20even%20as%20the%20company%20pours%20money%20into%20major%20investments%20elsewhere%2C%20BI%20previously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-retail-ceo-urges-cost-cuts-to-fund-big-new-investments-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20keep%20reducing%20costs%20so%20that%20we%20can%20afford%20the%20big%20investments%20in%20big%20new%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Herrington%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aekim%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eekim%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%2C%20Telegram%2C%20or%20WhatsApp%20at%20650-942-3061.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-freezes-hiring-budget-retail-business-this-year-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749228135000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22