ty.%20You%E2%80%99ll%20often%20see%20it%20at%20pride%20parades%2C%20marches%2C%20and%20events%20that%20support%20LGBTQ%2B%20rights.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20rainbow%20flags%20can%20also%20be%20used%20in%20other%20contexts%20(like%20peace%20movements)%2C%20within%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20a%20vibrant%20reminder%20that%20everyone%20deserves%20to%20be%20proud%20of%20who%20they%20are%20and%20to%20be%20treated%20with%20dignity%20and%20respect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECloseted%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomeone%20who%20is%20closeted%20isn%E2%80%99t%20openly%20sharing%20their%20sexual%20orientation%20or%20gender%20identity%20with%20others.%20Coming%20out%20is%20a%20personal%20choice%3B%20everyone%20has%20their%20own%20timing%20and%20comfort%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20person%20might%20be%20out%20to%20some%20close%20friends%2C%20but%20not%20to%20family%20or%20coworkers.%20Fear%20of%20rejection%2C%20being%20treated%20differently%2C%20losing%20their%20job%2C%20or%20even%20facing%20harassment%20or%20violence%20are%20some%20of%20the%20reasons%20why%20one%20is%20still%20%E2%80%98not%20out%2C%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20and%20that%20is%20how%20we%20should%20be%20saying%20it%2C%20%E2%80%98not%20out.%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EComing%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImagine%20carrying%20a%20beautiful%20book%20with%20you%20that%20only%20you%20have%20read.%20The%20pages%20hold%20stories%20of%20who%20you%20are%2C%20what%20you%20feel%2C%20and%20who%20you%20love.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F443704%2Fjackielynn-pradhan-trans-miss-universe-sikkim-lgbtq-pride%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EComing%20out%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20simply%20choosing%2C%20when%20you%E2%80%99re%20ready%2C%20to%20share%20that%20book%20with%20others.%20Maybe%20you%20read%20it%20aloud%20to%20a%20friend.%20Maybe%20you%20lend%20a%20page%20or%20two%20to%20someone%20you%20trust.%20Or%20maybe%2C%20for%20now%2C%20you%20just%20keep%20reading%20it%20quietly%20to%20yourself!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20out%20is%20not%20a%20one-time%20event.%20It%20is%20a%20lifelong%20process%20of%20self-understanding%20and%20(sometimes)%20self-sharing.%20Some%20people%20feel%20ready%20to%20tell%20others%3B%20some%20don%E2%80%99t%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20okay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EGender%20and%20gender%20dysphoria%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGender%20is%20not%20just%20about%20biology!%20It%20is%20about%20how%20we%20experience%20and%20express%20ourselves%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20the%20social%20and%20cultural%20idea%20of%20being%20%E2%80%9Cmasculine%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9Cfeminine%2C%E2%80%9D%20or%20somewhere%20in%20between%20(or%20beyond!).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20you%20might%20have%20been%20assigned%20%E2%80%9Cmale%E2%80%9D%20at%20birth%20based%20on%20your%20body%2C%20but%20inside%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20always%20felt%20more%20connected%20to%20being%20female%20%E2%80%94%20or%20maybe%20neither%20or%20both!%20That%20feeling%20is%20tied%20to%20your%20gender%20identity%2C%20which%20can%20be%20different%20from%20your%20assigned%20sex.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20when%20someone%E2%80%99s%20gender%20identity%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20match%20the%20sex%20they%20were%20assigned%20at%20birth%2C%20they%20might%20experience%20something%20called%20%3Cem%3Egender%20dysphoria.%3C%2Fem%3E%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20about%20being%20confused%20%E2%80%94%20it%20is%20about%20the%20emotional%20discomfort%20or%20distress%20that%20can%20come%20from%20that%20mismatch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20someone%20might%20strongly%20wish%20to%20be%20seen%20and%20treated%20as%20a%20different%20gender%2C%20or%20they%20might%20feel%20deeply%20uncomfortable%20with%20their%20body%20because%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20reflect%20who%20they%20are%20inside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ESide%20note%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20not%20all%20transgender%20or%20nonbinary%20people%20experience%20gender%20dysphoria%2C%20and%20those%20who%20do%20aren%E2%80%99t%20%E2%80%9Cbroken!%E2%80%9D%20They%E2%80%99re%20simply%20trying%20to%20live%20in%20a%20world%20that%20often%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20understand%20them.%20What%20matters%20most%20is%20supporting%20each%20person%E2%80%99s%20journey%20with%20respect%2C%20kindness%2C%20and%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-7-1749190053.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nonbinary%20is%20an%20umbrella%20term%20that%20encompasses%20various%20identities%2C%20including%20agender%2C%20bigender%2C%20and%20demigender.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-7-1749190053.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-7-1749190053-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-7-1749190053-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-7-1749190053-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-7-1749190053-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-445166%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENonbinary%20is%20an%20umbrella%20term%20that%20encompasses%20various%20identities%2C%20including%20agender%2C%20bigender%2C%20and%20demigender.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIntersex%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20intersex%20person%20is%20born%20with%20one%20or%20more%20innate%20sex%20characteristics%2C%20such%20as%20their%20sex%20organs%2C%20hormones%2C%20or%20chromosomes%2C%20that%20don%E2%80%99t%20fit%20into%20the%20typical%20definitions%20of%20what%E2%80%99s%20usually%20considered%20%E2%80%9Cmasculine%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cfeminine%E2%80%9D%20bodies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20a%20baby%20who%20is%20not%20born%20with%20XX%20or%20XY%2C%20but%20has%20some%20variations%20like%20XXY%20or%20XO%2C%20can%20influence%20how%20their%20bodies%20develop.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20further%20understand%2C%20some%20people%20might%20have%20chromosomes%20usually%20linked%20to%20boys%20(called%20XY)%2C%20but%20their%20bodies%20look%20more%20like%20girls.%20Others%20might%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F287639%2Flessons-i-learned-from-my-brother-with-down-syndrome-sibling%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echromosomes%3C%2Fa%3E%20usually%20linked%20to%20girls%20(XX)%20but%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20certain%20body%20parts%20like%20a%20uterus.%20Some%20babies%20are%20born%20with%20body%20parts%20that%20aren%E2%80%99t%20clearly%20one%20way%20or%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20know%20that%20being%20intersex%20is%3Cem%3E%20about%20the%20body%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20not%20about%20who%20someone%20feels%20inside%20or%20who%20they%20love.%20Some%20intersex%20people%20might%20also%20be%20transgender%2C%20meaning%20their%3Cem%3E%20inner%20sense%20of%20gender%3C%2Fem%3E%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20match%20how%20they%20were%20raised.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBut%20most%20intersex%20people%20aren%E2%80%99t%20transgender%2C%20and%20most%20transgender%20people%20aren%E2%80%99t%20intersex.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EOut%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20someone%20is%20out%2C%20it%20means%20they%20are%20open%20about%20being%20LGBTQ%2B%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20at%20home%20with%20family%2C%20at%20work%2C%20on%20social%20media%2C%20or%20in%20public%20spaces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20being%20%E2%80%9Cout%E2%80%9D%20looks%20different%20for%20everyone.%20Some%20people%20might%20be%20out%20only%20to%20close%20friends%20or%20family%2C%20while%20others%20might%20speak%20openly%20in%20public%20or%20on%20platforms%20to%20inspire%20others%20or%20push%20for%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Dutee%20Chand%2C%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%20sprinters%2C%20in%202019%2C%20became%20the%20first%20Indian%20athlete%20to%20publicly%20come%20out%20as%20lesbian.%20She%20shared%20that%20she%20was%20in%20a%20same-sex%20relationship%2C%20despite%20knowing%20that%20it%20might%20bring%20criticism%20and%20pressure.%20However%2C%20by%20coming%20out%2C%20Dutee%20not%20only%20lived%20her%20truth%20but%20also%20gave%20courage%20to%20others%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESide%20note%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EComing%20out%20should%20not%20be%20confused%20with%20another%20term%20known%20as%20%3Cem%3Eouting%2C%20which%20is%20the%20act%20of%20revealing%20another%20person%E2%80%99s%20sexual%20orientation%20or%20gender%20identity%20without%20their%20permission.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Sometimes%20it%20can%20be%20done%20based%20on%20rumours%20or%20assumptions.%20It%20is%20not%20considered%20appropriate%20even%20when%20the%20intentions%20are%20good%20because%20it%20simply%20takes%20away%20one%E2%80%99s%20choice%20and%20their%20control%20and%20can%20even%20put%20them%20at%20risk%20of%20discrimination%2C%20rejection%20or%20worse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESay%20this%2C%20not%20that%3A%20terms%20you%20should%20avoid%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20thoughtful%2C%20inclusive%20language%20shows%20respect%20and%20helps%20create%20a%20world%20where%20everyone%20feels%20seen%20and%20valued%2C%20which%20we%20can%20all%20support.%20Here%20are%20some%20ways%20that%20we%20can%20keep%20in%20mind%20while%20writing%20about%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community%20and%20try%20our%20best%20to%20avoid%20ambiguous%20ideas%20and%20concepts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20say%20%E2%80%9Chermaphrodite%2C%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20say%20%E2%80%9Cintersex%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20term%20hermaphrodite%20is%20outdated%20and%20considered%20offensive.%20It%20wrongly%20suggests%20that%20someone%20has%20fully%20formed%20male%20and%20female%20reproductive%20systems%2C%20which%20is%20medically%20inaccurate%20and%20stigmatising.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20use%20%E2%80%9Cintersex%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20is%20the%20respectful%20and%20accurate%20term%20for%20people%20born%20with%20physical%20sex%20traits%20that%20don%E2%80%99t%20fit%20typical%20male%20or%20female%20categories.%20Also%2C%20avoid%20calling%20Hijras%20%E2%80%9Chermaphrodites%E2%80%9D%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F390947%2Fnoori-mohammad-abuse-transwoman-hiv-positive-india-children-shelter%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHijras%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20are%20a%20distinct%20cultural%20and%20gender%20identity%20in%20South%20Asia%20and%20should%20be%20recognised%20on%20their%20own%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20say%20%E2%80%9Chomosexual%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Chomo%2C%E2%80%9D%20simply%20ask%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHomosexual%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20clinical%20term%20that%20feels%20cold%20and%20impersonal%20to%20many%20in%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community.%20The%20shortened%20version%20%E2%80%9Chomo%E2%80%9D%20is%20often%20used%20as%20a%20slur%20and%20is%20offensive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20ask%20how%20people%20would%20like%20to%20be%20addressed.%20These%20terms%20are%20affirming%20and%20widely%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20say%20%E2%80%9Chomosexual%20sex%2C%E2%80%9D%20say%20%E2%80%9Csex%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Crelationship%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20phrases%20like%20%E2%80%9Chomosexual%20sex%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cgay%20sex%E2%80%9D%20can%20feel%20dehumanising%20and%20overly%20clinical.%20Most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20enough%20to%20say%20%E2%80%9Csex%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9Crelationship%2C%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Ccouple%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAlso%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20describe%20homosexuality%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccondition%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F288700%2Fadhura-starring-irrfan-khan-in-queer-film-gay-character-banned-by-censor-board%2F%5C%22%3E%20homosexua%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F288700%2Fadhura-starring-irrfan-khan-in-queer-film-gay-character-banned-by-censor-board%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elity%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccondition%E2%80%9D%20wrongly%20suggests%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20disorder%20or%20illness%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20cured.%20That%20idea%20has%20been%20disproven%20and%20rejected%20by%20medical%20and%20psychological%20experts%20around%20the%20world.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHomosexuality%20is%20simply%20a%20natural%20variation%20of%20human%20sexuality.%20So%2C%20just%20talk%20about%20it%20as%20an%20orientation%20or%20identity%2C%20not%20a%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-8-1749190165.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Csexual%20preference%E2%80%9D%20should%20be%20avoided%20because%20it%20wrongly%20suggests%20that%20who%20someone%20is%20attracted%20to%20is%20just%20a%20choice%20like%20picking%20a%20favorite%20food.%20This%20idea%20has%20been%20used%20to%20support%20harmful%20beliefs%2C%20like%20trying%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfix%E2%80%9D%20or%20change%20someone%E2%80%99s%20sexuality%2C%20which%20is%20not%20only%20untrue%20but%20also%20very%20hurtful.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-8-1749190165.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-8-1749190165-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-8-1749190165-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-8-1749190165-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-8-1749190165-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-445169%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETransition%20is%20the%20personal%20process%20that%20someone%20goes%20through%20to%20help%20their%20gender%20expression%20and%2For%20their%20body%20better%20match%20their%20gender%20identity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20say%20%E2%80%9Csexual%20preference%2C%E2%80%9D%20say%20%E2%80%9Csexual%20orientation%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Csexual%20preference%E2%80%9D%20should%20be%20avoided%20because%20it%20wrongly%20suggests%20that%20who%20someone%20is%20attracted%20to%20is%20just%20a%20choice%20like%20picking%20a%20favorite%20food.%20This%20idea%20has%20been%20used%20to%20support%20harmful%20beliefs%2C%20like%20trying%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfix%E2%80%9D%20or%20change%20someone%E2%80%99s%20sexuality%2C%20which%20is%20not%20only%20untrue%20but%20also%20very%20hurtful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20right%20term%20to%20use%20is%20%E2%80%9Csexual%20orientation%E2%80%9D%20or%20just%20%E2%80%9Corientation.%E2%80%9D%20This%20refers%20to%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20natural%20and%20lasting%20attraction%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20to%20people%20of%20the%20same%20gender%2C%20a%20different%20gender%2C%20multiple%20genders%2C%20or%20none%20at%20all.%20It%20includes%20people%20who%20are%20lesbian%2C%20gay%2C%20bisexual%2C%20queer%2C%20pansexual%2C%20and%20also%20straight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20say%20%E2%80%9Clifestyle%2C%E2%80%9D%20say%20%E2%80%9CLGBTQI%2B%20people%20and%20their%20lives%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20word%20%E2%80%9Clifestyle%E2%80%9D%20usually%20describes%20the%20way%20people%20choose%20to%20live%2C%20like%20being%20busy%2C%20relaxed%2C%20eco-friendly%2C%20or%20sporty.%20It%20is%20about%20personal%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20people%20say%20%E2%80%9CLGBT%20lifestyle%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20wrongly%20suggests%20that%20being%20gay%2C%20lesbian%2C%20bi%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F436107%2Fbabli-by-night-bafta-neel-soni%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrans%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20choice%2C%20like%20picking%20a%20hobby%20or%20a%20trend.%20Being%20LGBTQI%2B%20is%20not%20a%20lifestyle%3B%20rather%2C%20it%20is%20who%20someone%20is.%20LGBTQI%2B%20people%20can%20have%20all%20kinds%20of%20lives%3A%20some%20are%20married%2C%20some%20have%20kids%2C%20some%20are%20single%2C%20and%20they%20live%20in%20all%20kinds%20of%20ways%2C%20just%20like%20anyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20say%20%E2%80%9Csex%20reassignment%20surgery%2C%E2%80%9D%20say%20%E2%80%9Ctransitioning%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETransition%20is%20the%20personal%20process%20that%20someone%20goes%20through%20to%20help%20their%20gender%20expression%20and%2For%20their%20body%20better%20match%20their%20gender%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20might%20include%20hormone%20therapy%20or%20surgeries.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20better%20to%20avoid%20terms%20like%20%E2%80%9Csex%20reassignment%20surgery%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20can%20sound%20outdated%20or%20overly%20focused%20on%20the%20body.%20Instead%2C%20just%20say%20%E2%80%9Ctransition%E2%80%9D%2C%20or%20talk%20about%20it%20in%20terms%20the%20person%20uses%3Cem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ESide%20note%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETransitioning%20is%20not%20just%20about%20medical%20changes.%20It%20can%20also%20include%20social%20and%20legal%20steps.%20This%20might%20mean%20coming%20out%20to%20family%20and%20friends%2C%20using%20a%20new%20name%20or%20pronouns%2C%20or%20changing%20how%20one%20dresses%20to%20reflect%20their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F248393%2Ffirst-transgender-band-yash-raj-films-komal-jagtap-transgender-rights-inspiring-india-gop94%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egender%20identity%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20can%20also%20involve%20updating%20documents%20like%20one%E2%80%99s%20driver%E2%80%99s%20license%2C%20passport%20and%20bank%20account%20to%20match%20the%20name%20and%20gender.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20transition%20is%20personal%2C%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20one%20%E2%80%9Cright%E2%80%9D%20way%20to%20do%20it%20%E2%80%94%20just%20the%20way%20that%20feels%20right!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPride%20Month%20is%20a%20time%20to%20celebrate%2C%20but%20it%20is%20also%20a%20moment%20to%20listen%2C%20learn%2C%20and%20grow.%20Understanding%20the%20words%20people%20use%20to%20describe%20themselves%20helps%20us%20show%20respect%20and%20kindness%20every%20day%2C%20not%20just%20in%20June.%20Let%20us%20embrace%20language%20with%20care%2C%20thus%20opening%20doors%20to%20acceptance%20and%20connection%2C%20helping%20everyone%20feel%20seen%20and%20valued%20just%20as%20they%20are!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EE