20chose%20to%20repair%2C%20not%20replace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20six%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20the%20shops%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F431994%2Flucknow-bioscope-sanatkada-begum-akhtar%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELucknow%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EChowk%20Bazaar%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewere%20still%20shuttered%20as%20we%20set%20off%20on%20our%20little%20adventure%2C%20joined%20by%20a%20bunch%20of%20like-minded%20folks%2C%20all%20curious%20and%20eager%20to%20freeze%20time%20through%20our%20lenses.%20As%20we%20walked%2C%20our%20organiser%20shared%20stories%20about%20the%20streets%2C%20including%20one%20about%20%3Cem%3EChor%20Bazaar%20(Thieves%E2%80%99%20Market)%20%3C%2Fem%3Enear%20Victoria%20Street.%20He%20told%20us%20it%20was%20once%20called%20%3Cem%3EShahi%20Bazaar%20(Royal%20Market)%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20place%20where%20people%20still%20buy%20old%20clothes%2C%20second-hand%20watches%2C%20and%20even%20get%20their%20transistors%20repaired.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20moment%20reminded%20me%20of%20how%20deeply%20ingrained%3Cem%3E%20jugaad%20%E2%80%94%3C%2Fem%3E%20India%E2%80%99s%20way%20of%20making%20do%20with%20what%E2%80%99s%20available%20%E2%80%94%20is%20in%20our%20culture.%20My%20mind%20drifted%20to%20memories%20of%20my%20mother%20taking%20my%20worn-out%20shoes%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3Emochi%20(cobbler)%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20stitching%2C%20or%20the%20%3Cem%3Ebartan%20wala%20%3C%2Fem%3E(utensil%20seller%20ot%20trader)%20who%20would%20roam%20our%20neighbourhood%2C%20trading%20old%20utensils%20for%20money.%20All%20signs%20of%20a%20quiet%20culture%20of%20repair%2C%20reuse%2C%20and%20sustainability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%222400846096%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20World%20Env